			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Tasch,<BR>
<BR>
Thanks for the accurate post about bards.  And the kind defense of our class.  You gotta get to lvl 60, brother, and start playing your bard again, we need all the good ones we can get out there!<BR>
<BR>
The good ones try, and suceed at getting their skills down, and at being versatile.  Thats what a bard is all about, versatility.<BR>
<BR>
We can wear plate armor, but the armor we get is NOT WHERE near the kind of plate warriors get, so we are often confused with tanks.  Frankly, while I can tank, I make a much better puller (though Monks are best at it, I believe).<BR>
<BR>
Bard basing is a popular sport on everlore.com<BR>
but thats no fault of the site or (mostly) the bards.  I havent figured out a reason for it yet, so I assign it under one of two catagories.<BR>
1) Jealousy<BR>
2) &quot;I played a bard and they suck.&quot; These people usually didnt play the bard for very long, or they have no idea how to properly play one.<BR>
<BR>
Why do you think the class is called &quot;bard&quot;?<BR>
Just a question for everyone out there, and please dont say &quot;Because they sing instead of cast&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
One reason, in my experience as a bard, is that, much like a guitar or mandolin player, or many musicians, it was chosen as a name because it places such *incredible* strain on our wrists and hands.  After 5 or 7 hours of playing my bard to his fullest, my wrists literally *ache*.<BR>
<BR>
I wonder if Jerry Garcia ever felt that way after a show...<BR>
<BR>
Best,<BR>
Gileas Dreamsinger, MM server, proud to be an Arcane Evol member, and bard of the 35th string.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
