				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Man when I saw evryone ripping on bards I had to post. NEVER INSULT A BARD!!!!! I am a rogue of the 55nd season and evryone at a high lvl can appreciate a bard at a higher lvl. There mana, there speed, there str, there evrything. There regen there mezzers there meelee and they are pretty dang good at all of them. There haste and str are the best in the game they can mez 3 on a good day. They replace both shammy and enchanters. They can fear, they can heal there selves after fights. I used to grp with a really nice 60 bard. Me and him could pull one after the other of spideres at velketor. He can just fear them and me and him run behind smacking the sh** out of it with dance of the blades on(a very nice str spell) and haste. Plus have you ever been a fat ugly ogre running through south karana on a cold windy day? Well bards just cast there invis super fast song of travel and your there in moments. They basically never die in the open while traveling. The armor they can wear isnt all that bad either they can get pretty high ac. Overall I would say a grp would pick a lower lvl bard over a higher lvl chanter. Unless they had severe train problems. Last night I had a chanter and bard in my grp it was pretty nice. Chanter was lvl 60 bard was lvl 54 55 now he dinged ) But they both played there classes very well kept em mezzed good etc. I'm just trying to say anyway that you do not want to flame bards, you are going to be so sorry one day. I have a lvl 30 bard I havent played in a while. When I get my rogue to 60 he'll be next class I play they have no problems getting grps never have downtime and in my opinion are the funnest class to play in the game. Just think about it.<BR>
<BR>
-Tarchannen Bladesmitten
